            <dc:language xsi:type="dcterms:ISO639-3">slv</dc:language>
            <dcterms:alternative xml:lang="eng">Migrations and Stereotypes</dcterms:alternative>
            <dcterms:alternative xml:lang="eng">The Case of the Optanti</dcterms:alternative>
            <dcterms:abstract xml:lang="slv">Avtor v svojem prispevku s pomočjo zgodovinskega primera skuša opozoriti na specifično oblikovanje stereotipov znotraj migracijskih procesov. Tipe migracij namreč določajo prostor, čas in motivacija, kar pa je večkrat težko določiti. Včasih prav zaradi posebnosti stereotipov, da za svoj nastanek potrebujejo določen čas, prostor in okolje, zgodovinski pogled postane nepogrešljiv pripomoček drugim družboslovnim in humanističnim vedam pri njihovem raziskovanju. Ta pristop se skuša preizkusiti na primeru pojma optanti, ko se zgodovinsko ozadje sooči z družboslovnim «definicijami stereotipa.</dcterms:abstract>
            <dcterms:abstract xml:lang="eng">Using his case study of the optanti as the basis for his research the author analyzes the formation of stereotypes within the process of migration. Migration types are namely defined by time, by locale, and by motivation, the last of which may be somewhat difficult to defìne. In order to be conceived, stereotypes need a certain place, a certain time, and specific circumstances. At this point, history with its peculiar view becomes an indispensable tool for the humanities and for other social disciplines in the course of their research. This approach was applied in the case study of the optanti in which the necessary historical background is confronted with definitions of a stereotype as it is perceived by the social sciences.</dcterms:abstract>
            <dcterms:isPartOf>Zbirka Zgodovinskega časopisa ; 32</dcterms:isPartOf>
